      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:5:18:3",
      "text": [
        " لَيْسَ فِي صِغَارِ الْإِبِلِ شَيْ‏ءٌ حَتَّى يَحُولَ عَلَيْهَا الْحَوْلُ مِنْ يَوْمِ تُنْتَجُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Umar Bin Azina, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said ‘There is nothing regarding the young camels until the year passes by over them from the day they were born’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ‘Umar ibn ’Udhaynah from Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Zakat is not due on camel’s young until one year passes from the day they are born.” (The following chapter seems to be the words of the compiler (rh)) "
        ]
      }
    },
